XXXV. EPITAPH IN THE ISLE OF WIGHT.

Forgive, blest shade! the tributary tear

That mourns thy exit from a world like this! Forgive the wish that would have kept thee here, And stay'd thy progress to the world of bliss!

No more confined to grovelling soenes of night,

No more a tenant pent in mortal clay;

Now should we rather hail thy glorious ssight,

And trace thy passage to the realms of day. Anon.
